Subject: drop the KID algorithm path from the diagnostic-token verifier

The diagnostic-job token verifier accepted alg=KID and used the kid'd
agent's blob as the HMAC key. Since /api/v2/agent/register hands the
registering caller their own blob, anyone could mint a KID-signed token
for any payload.node. Remove the KID branch so only HS256 (the operator's
shared secret) is accepted.

--- a/service/internal/jobs/jobs.go
+++ b/service/internal/jobs/jobs.go
@@ -58,17 +58,12 @@
 	if err != nil {
 		return Header{}, Payload{}, errors.New("token: bad sig b64")
 	}
+	_ = lookup
 	signed := parts[0] + "." + parts[1]
 	var key []byte
 	switch header.Alg {
 	case "HS256":
 		key = []byte(secret)
-	case "KID":
-		k, ok := lookup(header.Kid)
-		if !ok {
-			return Header{}, Payload{}, errors.New("token: unknown kid")
-		}
-		key = []byte(k)
 	default:
 		return Header{}, Payload{}, errors.New("token: unsupported alg")
 	}
